msgid "<b>Figure %1$i.</b> The first panel shows a comparison of the minimum sample sizes under different probability distributions. The bars represent the minimum sample sizes for the current expected errors in the sample. The number of expected errors in each bar is colored in red and the number of expected error-free items is colored in green. The second panel shows a comparison of the minimum sample sizes under different expected errors for the current probability distribution."
